{"questionId":"22752","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An infinite geometric sequence, with terms <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>, is such that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mtext>Σ</mtext><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>∞</mo></munderover><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the common ratio, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>, for the sequence.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22752","referenceCode":"21N.1.AHL.TZ0.6a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the common ratio, r, for the sequence.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}